status: Information about the source of a digital file important to the creation, use and management of digitally reformatted materials.

definition (en): Content (image, audio, or video) comprising the electronic resource has been created by digitization of the original item.
scope note (en): Common examples of original objects include: printed or manuscript texts and/or images that are made on paper or on vellum; photographic prints (and in some instances photographic negatives, depending on creator's intent); analog audio formats; and video formats. This value does not pertain to microform even if microform is the original.

definition (en): Content comprising the electronic resource has been created by scanning from microform.
scope note (en): 16mm microfilm, 35mm microfilm, 105mm microfiche, microcard, micro-opaque, etc.

preferred label (en): file reproduced from an electronic resource
definition (en): Electronic resource has been created or copied from an existing electronic resource.
scope note (en): E.g., to generate new copies or derivative copies with lower resolution or smaller file size; to process an existing file with Optical Character Recognition - OCR - software; etc.

preferred label (en): file reproduced from an intermediate   (not microform
definition (en): Content comprising the electronic resource has been created by reformatting/digitizing from an intermediate other than microform.
scope note (en): Common examples of non-microfom intermediates for visual and textual materials are: photocopies, 35 mm film, transparencies, slides, 2nd generation video tape, etc. A common example of an intermediate for audio materials is 2nd generation analog tapes.

definition (en): Images comprising the electronic resource have been created from mixed sources.
scope note (en): Portions scanned from original item, portions scanned from microfilm, etc.

definition (en): Antecedent or source are not applicable to this electronic resource.
scope note (en): Appropriate for electronic resources other than those created during a reformatting process.

definition (en): Antecedent or source of this reformatted electronic resource is not known.
